WEBVTT

00:07.050 --> 00:14.188
♪

00:14.318 --> 00:21.891
♪

00:22.022 --> 00:24.981
[ Crowd cheering on TV]

00:25.112 --> 00:26.287
Joe:
Murray catches a screen pass...

00:26.417 --> 00:28.376
Announcer:
Murray catches a screen pass...

00:28.506 --> 00:29.986
...and slides through
the Wolverine defense

00:30.117 --> 00:31.422
for 34 yards. ...and slides through

00:31.553 --> 00:33.511
the Wolverine defense
for 34 yards.

00:33.642 --> 00:35.992
[Gilligan whines]

00:36.123 --> 00:38.081
Again?
Why you always gotta take a leak

00:38.212 --> 00:41.128
on this weak-ass defense?

00:41.258 --> 00:43.739
[Sighs] Man.

00:45.175 --> 00:53.662
♪

00:53.792 --> 01:02.540
♪

01:02.671 --> 01:03.933
We're a go to pee.

01:04.064 --> 01:05.326
[Gilligan barks quietly]

01:05.456 --> 01:10.853
♪

01:10.983 --> 01:16.641
♪

01:16.772 --> 01:19.905
You know, Gilligan, some things
are still nice, huh?

01:20.036 --> 01:27.652
♪

01:27.783 --> 01:35.269
♪

01:35.399 --> 01:43.146
♪

01:43.277 --> 01:44.843
Go. Here we go.

01:44.974 --> 01:47.019
Touchdown! Yeah!

01:47.150 --> 01:49.152
Yes! Yes![Gilligan barks]

01:49.283 --> 01:51.285
That's how we do it!

01:51.415 --> 01:54.070
I know. Crazy.

01:54.201 --> 01:57.595
♪

02:03.862 --> 02:06.038
[Gilligan whines]

02:06.169 --> 02:08.911
Gotta keep the old noggin sharp.

02:09.041 --> 02:12.567
[Gilligan whines]

02:12.697 --> 02:14.656
The hell?

02:14.786 --> 02:15.526
[Sighs]

02:15.657 --> 02:17.615
Gilly.

02:17.746 --> 02:20.618
There's nothing wrong
with getting older.

02:20.749 --> 02:23.186
Come on.
Let's finish this outside.

02:28.017 --> 02:36.460
♪

02:36.591 --> 02:45.208
♪

02:45.339 --> 02:46.992
[Herd growling]

02:47.123 --> 02:47.993
[Gilligan growls]

02:48.124 --> 02:49.865
I hear 'em, Gilly.

02:49.995 --> 02:51.214
[Gilligan barks]

02:54.522 --> 02:56.567
♪

02:56.698 --> 02:58.352
[Gilligan barks]

02:58.482 --> 03:00.441
Easy, Gilly.
We don't want more coming.

03:00.571 --> 03:02.182
[Herd growling]

03:02.312 --> 03:11.800
♪

03:11.930 --> 03:13.932
[Gilligan yelps]

03:14.063 --> 03:15.586
♪

03:15.717 --> 03:17.719
No! No!

03:17.849 --> 03:26.467
♪

03:26.597 --> 03:34.953
♪

03:35.084 --> 03:43.397
♪

03:43.527 --> 03:52.319
♪

03:52.449 --> 03:55.452
[ Whistle blows,
crowd cheering on TV]

03:55.583 --> 04:04.418
♪

04:04.548 --> 04:13.644
♪

04:13.775 --> 04:22.871
♪

04:23.001 --> 04:25.787
Aah!

04:25.917 --> 04:30.182
♪

04:46.895 --> 04:48.723
Joe: "Hey, USHLDBSCRD.
[you should be scared]

04:48.853 --> 04:50.202
What'll happen first:

04:50.333 --> 04:52.379
the world ends
or I pay off my shelter?"

04:52.509 --> 04:55.773
USHLDBSCRD: "DotTheEye,
my hubs would leave me

04:55.904 --> 04:58.385
if he knew I upgraded
to a platinum bunker."

04:59.908 --> 05:02.171
Joe: "My sister thinks
I'm too depressed."

05:02.302 --> 05:03.912
USHLDBSCRD: "Let me tell ya,

05:04.042 --> 05:06.436
she's the one who's
not seeing things clearly.

05:06.567 --> 05:09.439
You and I,
we're just getting ready.

05:09.570 --> 05:12.050
My husband, Tom,
he passed last month.

05:12.181 --> 05:13.051
I'm alone now."

05:13.182 --> 05:14.531
Joe: "I'm so sorry.

05:14.662 --> 05:17.273
But you got me.
Digitally, at least."

05:17.404 --> 05:20.145
USHLDBSCRD: "You're the only one
who gets me.

05:20.276 --> 05:22.060
Let's meet IRL."

05:22.191 --> 05:24.585
"I feel the same.

05:24.715 --> 05:26.326
But meeting?"

05:28.893 --> 05:30.678
USHLDBSCRD:
"Are you afraid?"

05:33.158 --> 05:35.030
Goddamn coward.

05:36.597 --> 05:39.817
USHLDBSCRD: "I'm surrounded
by Wolverine fans.

05:39.948 --> 05:41.602
Lots of factory boys here."

05:41.732 --> 05:48.870
♪

05:49.000 --> 05:56.356
♪

06:00.577 --> 06:01.622
[Door shuts]

06:01.752 --> 06:09.194
♪

06:09.325 --> 06:16.767
♪

06:16.898 --> 06:24.558
♪

06:24.688 --> 06:28.039
[Engine starts, whirs quietly]

06:28.170 --> 06:29.650
You made it.

06:29.780 --> 06:32.696
When everybody else didn't.

06:32.827 --> 06:34.350
The hell you doing?

06:34.481 --> 06:42.184
♪

06:42.314 --> 06:50.148
♪

06:50.279 --> 06:51.759
Should've gone underground.

06:51.889 --> 07:00.550
♪

07:01.986 --> 07:04.641
[Tires hissing]

07:04.772 --> 07:06.338
Shit!

07:09.603 --> 07:12.432
♪

07:12.562 --> 07:13.911
Oh!

07:14.042 --> 07:15.913
[Bell ringing]

07:18.263 --> 07:20.701
[Walker growling]

07:20.831 --> 07:26.620
♪

07:26.750 --> 07:33.148
♪

07:38.675 --> 07:41.112
May your next life be blessed.

07:41.243 --> 07:42.723
[Bell ringing]Hey.

07:42.853 --> 07:46.944
You're ringing a dinner bell
for the toe-tags.

07:47.075 --> 07:49.512
Alright, you got a blade?

07:49.643 --> 07:51.949
Tell me. I'm not looking
to open up an artery here.

07:52.080 --> 07:53.821
Yours or mine.

07:56.084 --> 07:56.954
Oh.

08:01.219 --> 08:02.960
A switchblade. Quaint.

08:05.006 --> 08:06.094
Couldn't reach it, huh?

08:06.224 --> 08:08.313
Too much time on weights
instead of core?

08:08.444 --> 08:09.358
My core is fine.

08:09.489 --> 08:10.968
It's your tight-ass net.

08:11.099 --> 08:13.710
What the hell is this thing?

08:13.841 --> 08:16.974
Well, put these on,
and I'll let you down.

08:17.105 --> 08:18.541
And if I don't?

08:18.672 --> 08:20.674
I can leave. Your choice.

08:20.804 --> 08:23.546
Cuffed and sheltered,
or human piñata?

08:23.677 --> 08:28.420
♪

08:31.815 --> 08:34.383
Evie: This couldn't have
happened at a better time.

08:34.514 --> 08:35.645
The weather's still good,

08:35.776 --> 08:38.213
and honestly,
you answered my prayers.

08:40.084 --> 08:42.522
Now, I don't want you to feel
that, when I leave,

08:42.652 --> 08:44.132
that you got a raw deal.

08:44.262 --> 08:45.960
This place is end-times-ready.

08:46.090 --> 08:48.353
There's a greenhouse
on a greywater system,

08:48.484 --> 08:50.442
with lots of organic vegetables.

08:50.573 --> 08:53.881
Although, I know everything's
organic now, right?

08:54.011 --> 08:56.231
But, you know, we were
organic before that.

08:56.361 --> 08:57.928
We also have a ton
of weed plants.

08:58.059 --> 09:01.366
Natch.
It's one of my hobbies.

09:01.497 --> 09:02.803
Look, I don't want to be
too Pollyanna,

09:02.933 --> 09:05.283
but if there was ever
an ideal situation

09:05.414 --> 09:09.549
to have your bike stolen,
I mean, this is it.

09:09.679 --> 09:11.028
Good luck driving it.

09:11.159 --> 09:13.204
Oh, you think because I have
two X chromosomes,

09:13.335 --> 09:15.032
I can't handle a hog?
[Chuckles]

09:15.163 --> 09:17.208
I've had worse
between my legs.

09:17.339 --> 09:19.036
It's got a kill switch.

09:19.167 --> 09:20.690
Designed by moi.

09:22.083 --> 09:25.347
And now I know,
so I'll figure it out, Monsieur.

09:25.477 --> 09:27.262
But you won't.

09:28.959 --> 09:31.701
Well, then you just became
my involuntary chauffeur.

09:31.832 --> 09:35.662
Once you get me to wherever
I need to go, you can take off.

09:35.792 --> 09:38.229
Besides...
it's not a request.

09:39.622 --> 09:42.059
That doesn't seem like
a vegan's kind of gun.

09:42.190 --> 09:45.019
Well, I haven't
gone vegan yet.

09:45.149 --> 09:47.848
Why do you want
to leave here anyway?

09:47.978 --> 09:49.632
Why did you leave
yourplace?

09:49.763 --> 09:50.764
How do you know
I had one?

09:50.894 --> 09:52.287
Because you're clean.

09:52.417 --> 09:54.115
And your bike has
some pretty impressive mods,

09:54.245 --> 09:57.118
which would have been hard to do
after the world went down.

09:57.248 --> 09:59.250
Am I warm?

09:59.381 --> 10:01.252
Which is why
I'm still here kickin'

10:01.383 --> 10:03.646
and most everyone
else isn't.

10:03.777 --> 10:05.953
No one believed
this could happen.

10:06.083 --> 10:08.433
No one ever thinks
bad things will happen.

10:08.564 --> 10:10.479
But I was prepared,

10:10.610 --> 10:12.655
and I made sure
I stayed far enough away

10:12.786 --> 10:14.309
so nobody who wasn't

10:14.439 --> 10:16.528
couldn't come crying to me.

10:16.659 --> 10:18.530
Happy story, Mr. Sunshine.

10:18.661 --> 10:20.315
You just holed up
with your protein powder?

10:21.403 --> 10:23.100
Alright.

10:23.231 --> 10:25.363
Ready to go.

10:25.494 --> 10:26.495
What's your name?

10:27.888 --> 10:30.194
I don't think you want me
to come up with one.

10:30.325 --> 10:32.675
The nickname "P.P." is the only
thing coming to mind right now,

10:32.806 --> 10:33.937
so...

10:34.068 --> 10:35.809
Joe.

10:35.939 --> 10:37.462
Joe.

10:37.593 --> 10:38.768
Joe. Well...

10:40.640 --> 10:42.685
This is a gift for you.

10:42.816 --> 10:44.861
Come here. Okay.

10:44.992 --> 10:46.994
What the hell is this?

10:47.124 --> 10:50.127
Well, I'm hoping it dispels
some of your bad vibes. Yeah.

10:50.258 --> 10:52.173
I-I find that negative energy
has a tendency

10:52.303 --> 10:54.610
to draw negative energy,
so just, like...

10:54.741 --> 10:57.831
New age hippy bullshit.Oh, dear.

10:57.961 --> 11:00.268
Well, I didn't want to judge
a prepper by its cover, but...

11:00.398 --> 11:03.358
I'll say this,
you do a decent clove hitch.

11:03.488 --> 11:04.968
You got a father
in the military?

11:05.099 --> 11:06.840
Oh, you mean the net?
No.

11:06.970 --> 11:09.799
I just took a macramé intensive
in Big Sur once.

11:09.930 --> 11:11.583
I actually can't believe
it worked.

11:11.714 --> 11:12.933
You were so tight in there.

11:13.063 --> 11:16.110
Alright, we got a big drive
tomorrow. Rest up.

11:16.240 --> 11:24.945
♪

11:25.075 --> 11:27.164
Okay. In half a mile,
you'll want to take

11:27.295 --> 11:29.689
a small unmarked road
to your left.

11:29.819 --> 11:32.039
I'm not deviating
from my route.

11:32.169 --> 11:34.432
Well, then you'll be driving
straight into another trap.

11:34.563 --> 11:36.739
More than half the roads here
are either blown out or flooded.

11:36.870 --> 11:38.088
I know which ones.

11:38.219 --> 11:40.961
I mean, truth is,
you're lucky I'm here.

11:41.091 --> 11:42.876
So, what,
I'm supposed to be grateful?

11:43.006 --> 11:45.922
♪

11:46.053 --> 11:48.229
Hey.
Jesus.

11:48.359 --> 11:50.927
There's a sun glare,
trigger finger.

11:51.058 --> 11:52.929
Keep your hands
on the steering.

11:53.060 --> 11:59.719
♪

11:59.849 --> 12:02.591
Hey, you're a Doberman guy?

12:02.722 --> 12:03.897
Indeed.

12:04.027 --> 12:05.986
I used to work
at an animal shelter once.

12:06.116 --> 12:08.553
Super cool dogs,
and sharp, loyal.

12:08.684 --> 12:09.685
So dope.

12:09.816 --> 12:12.470
♪

12:12.601 --> 12:13.907
Yeah.

12:14.037 --> 12:19.042
♪

12:19.173 --> 12:20.348
[Engine starts, whirs]

12:20.478 --> 12:29.313
♪

12:29.444 --> 12:38.148
♪

12:38.279 --> 12:47.070
♪

12:47.201 --> 12:55.862
♪

12:55.992 --> 12:57.037
Why are you stopping?

12:58.778 --> 13:00.823
Mother nature calls.

13:02.390 --> 13:03.521
Are you serious?

13:03.652 --> 13:05.480
Sorry.
You'll have to make do.

13:12.400 --> 13:13.705
Thank you.

13:23.933 --> 13:26.806
I used to love driving.[Peeing]

13:26.936 --> 13:29.069
I had a convertible Saab
my aunt gave me.

13:29.199 --> 13:31.723
I lived with the top down.

13:33.334 --> 13:35.684
Do you mind?
I need to concentrate.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.947
[Peeing continues]

13:41.995 --> 13:43.300
[Zipper zips]

13:58.272 --> 14:00.709
Okay, so, in six miles,
you're gonna want to --

14:00.840 --> 14:02.754
[Charlie Pride's "Kiss an Angel
Good Mornin'"playing]

14:02.885 --> 14:07.020
♪ Some of them never learn
it's a simple thing♪

14:07.150 --> 14:10.284
♪

14:10.414 --> 14:11.676
[Engine starts, whirs]

14:11.807 --> 14:14.418
♪ Whenever I've chance to meet♪

14:14.549 --> 14:17.508
♪ Some old friends
on the street, they wonder♪

14:17.639 --> 14:22.992
[Off-key] ♪ How does a man
get to be this way? ♪

14:24.254 --> 14:28.780
♪ I've always got
a smilin' face ♪

14:28.911 --> 14:31.827
♪ Kiss an angel
good mornin' ♪

14:31.958 --> 14:36.832
♪ Love her like the devil
when you get back ho-- ♪

14:36.963 --> 14:40.009
♪ Kiss an angel good mornin'♪

14:40.140 --> 14:44.666
♪ And let her know you think
about her when you're gone♪

14:47.321 --> 14:49.976
You're gonna nick the blade up
doing it like that.

14:50.106 --> 14:52.065
You need to do it
in one smooth motion.

14:52.195 --> 14:54.371
I've had no problems
killing toe-tags yet.

14:58.506 --> 14:59.942
[Smooth scraping]

15:12.215 --> 15:14.609
You know, you wouldn't
have to do everything alone

15:14.739 --> 15:16.741
if you exercised
a little trust.

15:16.872 --> 15:19.135
I worked construction.

15:19.266 --> 15:20.963
I know things.

15:21.094 --> 15:23.400
I'd like to, Joe,
but what do I know about you?

15:23.531 --> 15:25.881
You worked construction.
Allegedly.

15:26.012 --> 15:27.796
You can pimp out a bike?
Maybe.

15:27.927 --> 15:30.146
You will butcher a Charlie Pride
song? Definitely.

15:36.587 --> 15:37.893
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

15:38.024 --> 15:40.200
What the hell
are you doing?

15:40.330 --> 15:42.071
Seeing who you are.

15:51.863 --> 15:53.169
Very prepared.

15:56.912 --> 15:58.435
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Stop it.

15:58.566 --> 15:59.654
Stop it.

15:59.784 --> 16:01.221
You want me to trust you.

16:01.351 --> 16:03.005
People only carry
important things now.

16:03.136 --> 16:05.094
Put that away,
you nosy bitch.

16:09.229 --> 16:11.100
Why? What am I
gonna find in here?

16:11.231 --> 16:13.450
Do you have friends
waiting for me along the route?

16:13.581 --> 16:15.017
Worse?

16:15.148 --> 16:17.237
[Paper rustling]

16:17.367 --> 16:20.370
"We see eye to eye
on so much.

16:20.501 --> 16:22.590
We don't think the world
is going to shit.

16:22.720 --> 16:24.244
We're not crazy.

16:24.374 --> 16:27.769
We're just prepared
because we're survivors.

16:27.899 --> 16:30.424
I wish we lived closer.

16:30.554 --> 16:34.167
But hope is the thing
with feathers."

16:34.297 --> 16:36.734
Puppies and poetry?

16:36.865 --> 16:38.388
Who are you?

16:38.519 --> 16:40.608
♪

16:40.738 --> 16:43.045
None of your business.

16:43.176 --> 16:47.093
♪

16:47.223 --> 16:49.182
You're right.

16:49.312 --> 16:50.270
I'm sorry.

16:50.400 --> 16:53.360
♪

16:53.490 --> 16:54.883
You know, if it makes you feel
any better,

16:55.014 --> 16:57.320
I'm on the road
for love, too.

16:57.451 --> 16:58.756
In a way.

16:58.887 --> 17:07.591
♪

17:07.722 --> 17:16.426
♪

17:16.557 --> 17:25.522
♪

17:28.003 --> 17:35.097
♪

17:35.228 --> 17:42.452
♪

17:42.583 --> 17:49.590
♪

17:49.720 --> 17:50.765
See, Joe?

17:52.593 --> 17:54.247
Just when I think
there's nothing left,

17:54.377 --> 17:56.466
the world reminds me
there's still magic.

17:56.597 --> 17:59.208
[Scoffs]
There's no magic.

17:59.339 --> 18:01.776
You're holding a Glock on me,
and we just saw two dead people

18:01.906 --> 18:04.126
stumbling around
with maggots on their faces.

18:04.257 --> 18:08.609
♪

18:08.739 --> 18:10.219
I'm sorry.

18:12.874 --> 18:15.268
Some things arestill nice.

18:15.398 --> 18:21.100
♪

18:25.626 --> 18:27.889
[Bells jingling]

18:30.065 --> 18:32.546
♪

18:32.676 --> 18:34.809
[Herd growling]

18:36.245 --> 18:38.029
You got to let me fight.

18:39.596 --> 18:42.643
Evie, listen to that.
It's coming from all sides.

18:42.773 --> 18:43.687
Take off the cuffs.

18:43.818 --> 18:52.957
♪

18:53.088 --> 18:55.743
[Herd continues growling]

18:55.873 --> 19:03.838
♪

19:07.189 --> 19:09.887
[Herd growling]

19:10.018 --> 19:18.766
♪

19:18.896 --> 19:27.688
♪

19:27.818 --> 19:29.472
Joe!

19:29.603 --> 19:31.909
[Grunts]

19:32.040 --> 19:40.179
♪

19:40.309 --> 19:48.404
♪

19:48.535 --> 19:50.145
[Growling stops]

19:50.276 --> 19:53.235
[Both panting]

19:53.366 --> 19:56.064
Damn.
You study martial arts?

19:56.195 --> 19:58.240
Capoeira.

19:58.371 --> 20:00.677
Sounds like a drink.

20:00.808 --> 20:02.070
It's Brazilian.

20:04.812 --> 20:06.466
Someone took
its heart out.

20:08.381 --> 20:10.078
I hope it happened
after they turned.

20:13.342 --> 20:15.214
May your next lives
be blessed.

20:18.782 --> 20:23.613
♪

20:23.744 --> 20:25.963
I love you
in bracelets, but...

20:26.094 --> 20:32.056
♪

20:32.187 --> 20:34.450
Should we hit the road?

20:36.060 --> 20:37.801
You in the mood to drive?

20:39.890 --> 20:40.891
[Chuckles]

20:41.022 --> 20:43.154
♪ You've got to♪

20:43.285 --> 20:45.766
♪ Kiss an angel good mornin' ♪ Kiss an angel good mornin'

20:45.896 --> 20:50.988
♪ And love her like the devil
when you get back home ♪

20:51.119 --> 20:54.296
♪ Kiss an angel good mornin' ♪ Kiss an angel good mornin'

20:54.427 --> 20:57.604
♪ And let her know you think
about her when you're gone ♪

20:57.734 --> 21:06.134
♪

21:06.265 --> 21:07.527
Joe: Ooh!

21:07.657 --> 21:09.442
Hit the lotto.

21:09.572 --> 21:11.400
Thank you to the worker

21:11.531 --> 21:14.098
with a weak spot
for the bourbon.

21:14.229 --> 21:16.710
Oh. Enjoy.
I don't drink.

21:16.840 --> 21:18.755
Just weed.

21:18.886 --> 21:21.149
Mm.
You like orange juice?

21:21.280 --> 21:23.194
From what I remember.

21:23.325 --> 21:25.153
Well, I don't have
the real stuff.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.547
I have the powder
in my bag.

21:27.677 --> 21:30.376
Here.

21:30.506 --> 21:33.248
Have at.

21:33.379 --> 21:35.381
So...

21:35.511 --> 21:38.775
where exactly
am I taking you?

21:38.906 --> 21:39.950
Mount Pleasant.

21:40.081 --> 21:42.823
No kidding.

21:42.953 --> 21:45.565
That's less than 10 miles
from where I'm headed.

21:45.695 --> 21:48.829
I mean, seriously,
what are the odds?

21:49.917 --> 21:52.398
The fact that we came
into each other's lives.

21:52.528 --> 21:54.922
That's the universe
showing us more magic.

21:55.052 --> 21:57.577
"The Universe"?

21:57.707 --> 22:00.493
You really think "The Universe"
gives a shit about us?

22:00.623 --> 22:03.452
Why do you waste your time
on that crap?

22:03.583 --> 22:05.280
You've got great
survivor skills,

22:05.411 --> 22:08.196
and you are
an equipped woman

22:08.327 --> 22:10.329
prepared to handle
this shit.

22:10.459 --> 22:14.333
The Universe
made me into this.

22:14.463 --> 22:17.074
I mean, I didn't
have it together before.

22:17.205 --> 22:20.251
I mean, everybody around me --
family, friends, my husband --

22:20.382 --> 22:23.385
all of them, in their own way,
told me that I was lost.

22:23.516 --> 22:24.865
You got a husband?

22:24.995 --> 22:26.170
Mm. Sort of.

22:26.301 --> 22:29.173
We separated
just before...

22:29.304 --> 22:31.611
We actually met
at an inner-discovery retreat.

22:31.741 --> 22:35.789
It's like yoga, water therapy,
animal therapy,

22:35.919 --> 22:38.444
art therapy.

22:38.574 --> 22:40.271
We came away
with each other.

22:40.402 --> 22:42.578
But he also came away
with something that helped him

22:42.709 --> 22:45.146
get rid
of his energy vampires,

22:45.276 --> 22:49.237
a way to flush out his demons
with pastels and brushstrokes.

22:49.368 --> 22:50.412
Wait, what?

22:50.543 --> 22:52.545
It's, uh, hatin' paintin'.

22:52.675 --> 22:54.634
Yeah, so, he would paint
people who pissed him off

22:54.764 --> 22:57.854
or betrayed him
or disappointed him somehow.

22:57.985 --> 22:59.769
You should've
got him a crystal.

22:59.900 --> 23:00.857
Oh, I did.

23:00.988 --> 23:02.381
I did a lot for him.

23:02.511 --> 23:03.817
You know, I loved him.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.906
I think.

23:06.036 --> 23:08.125
So, if he put me
on a canvas,

23:08.256 --> 23:10.345
then that would
kind of hurt.

23:10.476 --> 23:12.434
You think he painted you?

23:15.698 --> 23:17.265
We said a lot of mean things
to each other

23:17.396 --> 23:19.659
the last time we talked.

23:19.789 --> 23:21.051
My friend was starting
that organic farm,

23:21.182 --> 23:22.488
and I wanted to help.

23:22.618 --> 23:25.360
He said if I left,
then he would, too.

23:25.491 --> 23:29.843
Move to his family's cabin
and do a series on me.

23:29.973 --> 23:31.584
♪

23:31.714 --> 23:34.108
It's been more than a year
since the end.

23:34.238 --> 23:36.850
Are you sure Steven is still
where you think he is?

23:36.980 --> 23:38.678
I don't know.

23:38.808 --> 23:42.290
But I gotta give it a try,
right?

23:42.421 --> 23:46.729
I'd been waiting for a miracle
to take me there.

23:46.860 --> 23:48.252
And then you came.

23:48.383 --> 23:53.867
♪

23:53.997 --> 23:57.784
Maybe since
you know the area,

23:57.914 --> 24:00.700
you could help me find
exactly where she is.

24:00.830 --> 24:03.572
♪

24:03.703 --> 24:07.924
It gets a little personal,
but...

24:08.055 --> 24:09.752
I guess I trust you.

24:09.883 --> 24:15.497
♪

24:23.766 --> 24:24.767
[Engine starts, whirs]

24:24.898 --> 24:26.508
We're ready!

24:26.639 --> 24:29.685
Evie: [In distance]
Wait! Come here a sec!

24:29.816 --> 24:31.774
Joe! You gotta
check this out!

24:31.905 --> 24:33.776
Come here!

24:33.907 --> 24:36.866
What do you want?She says, "Tired of hipsters

24:36.997 --> 24:39.086
waiting on line
by my house.

24:39.216 --> 24:42.698
A gluten-free donut place
opened up on the corner."

24:42.829 --> 24:44.613
"A" -- it's inline.

24:44.744 --> 24:46.180
"B" -- she doesn't know
what she's missing,

24:46.310 --> 24:49.923
'cause, "C" -- I think she's
talking about Idyll Fonuts.

24:50.053 --> 24:52.142
And I think I know
where it is.

24:52.273 --> 24:53.579
Are you serious?Yeah.

24:53.709 --> 24:55.972
I got a photo of her house
right here.

24:58.540 --> 25:01.543
I helped her decide on a new
wagon when she was looking.

25:01.674 --> 25:03.371
You seem perfect
for each other.

25:05.591 --> 25:07.984
Well, if the weather holds,

25:08.115 --> 25:10.421
and we get a little lucky
with the toe-tags,

25:10.552 --> 25:12.772
we should be able to be there
in less than 12 hours.

25:15.165 --> 25:16.079
Wow.

25:16.210 --> 25:17.733
♪

25:17.864 --> 25:20.040
You know, uh,

25:20.170 --> 25:22.346
this is the most time
I've spent with anyone

25:22.477 --> 25:24.566
in years, I mean,

25:24.697 --> 25:25.915
other than Gilligan.

25:26.046 --> 25:28.135
♪

25:28.265 --> 25:30.137
Um...

25:30.267 --> 25:33.444
it's been nice.

25:33.575 --> 25:37.231
I mean, not how it started,
but now.

25:37.361 --> 25:39.712
[Lamb bleats]

25:39.842 --> 25:40.800
What the hell?

25:40.930 --> 25:43.019
♪

25:43.150 --> 25:45.718
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

25:45.848 --> 25:47.415
Where did you come from?

25:47.546 --> 25:49.678
"Thanks for the bike"?

25:49.809 --> 25:51.985
You poor thing.
Are you hungry?

25:53.160 --> 25:55.075
No! No, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

25:55.205 --> 25:56.424
[Lamb bleats]

25:57.512 --> 25:58.992
No, no, no, no!

26:00.123 --> 26:01.472
[Gun clicks]

26:06.086 --> 26:11.004
♪

26:14.616 --> 26:16.052
He took my helmet.

26:16.183 --> 26:17.314
Everything was
in the bike!

26:17.445 --> 26:20.013
Yeah.
So was my sloth.

26:20.143 --> 26:22.406
Well, now you have a lamb.
Happy?

26:22.537 --> 26:25.192
What about the "unbeatable"
kill switch designed by toi?

26:25.322 --> 26:27.455
It's not on
when it's running.

26:27.586 --> 26:29.239
Why did you
leave it running?

26:29.370 --> 26:31.154
Because you --

26:31.285 --> 26:33.635
you -- You!

26:35.768 --> 26:37.117
1980.

26:37.247 --> 26:38.640
Ohio State.

26:38.771 --> 26:40.816
Tim Spencer,
ranked fourth

26:40.947 --> 26:43.166
with 5.3 yards.

26:43.297 --> 26:47.083
We're walking targets out here
because you won't listen.

26:48.345 --> 26:49.695
Well, least
we have dinner.

26:49.825 --> 26:51.435
[Gasps]

26:51.566 --> 26:53.046
That's not even funny.

26:53.176 --> 26:54.656
No, look at her face.

26:54.787 --> 26:57.572
Look.
Look at her face.

26:57.703 --> 27:00.793
Sheep are a lot smarter
than we think, don't you know?

27:00.923 --> 27:03.143
They have cognitive skills
and form deep bonds.

27:03.273 --> 27:05.841
No, they stick up
for each other and grieve.

27:05.972 --> 27:07.364
They could be man's
second best friend

27:07.495 --> 27:09.410
if we just opened
our minds a little.

27:09.540 --> 27:11.238
Plus, cheese.

27:11.368 --> 27:12.631
[Lamb bleats]

27:12.761 --> 27:14.894
You people.

27:15.024 --> 27:18.245
You always think you're saving
the goddamn world.

27:18.375 --> 27:19.594
What now?

27:19.725 --> 27:21.335
You're a catastrophe.

27:21.465 --> 27:23.685
Everything I needed
was in there.

27:23.816 --> 27:24.904
Look.

27:25.034 --> 27:27.167
I'm sorry.
But you should've known

27:27.297 --> 27:29.256
that the gun
wasn't loaded.

27:29.386 --> 27:30.605
Why the hell would I?

27:30.736 --> 27:33.913
Because obviously
I hate guns.

27:34.043 --> 27:35.828
I should've
ditched you before,

27:35.958 --> 27:38.918
you and your
delusional mission.

27:39.048 --> 27:40.354
What does that mean?

27:40.484 --> 27:42.356
You are risking your life

27:42.486 --> 27:45.838
to see a goddamn asshole
and his painting.

27:45.968 --> 27:47.753
Maybe you really
do believe

27:47.883 --> 27:49.842
he knew you better
than you knew yourself.

27:49.972 --> 27:52.888
And if that's true,
and he painted you,

27:53.019 --> 27:55.761
then maybe
he was right about you!

27:55.891 --> 27:57.806
You're too naive!

27:57.937 --> 28:01.331
And you wanna know
my opinion?

28:01.462 --> 28:04.291
I'm on Team Steve here.

28:04.421 --> 28:07.729
What the hell do you understand
about relationships anyways?

28:09.426 --> 28:11.341
You want to be
a truth teller?

28:11.472 --> 28:13.779
Then be honest
with yourself.

28:13.909 --> 28:16.129
We both know that even if you
thought the gun was loaded,

28:16.259 --> 28:17.565
there were a lot
of opportunities

28:17.696 --> 28:19.436
for you to get away,
but you didn't want to

28:19.567 --> 28:21.395
because you're lonely, Joe.

28:21.525 --> 28:22.526
Keep telling yourself that --

28:22.657 --> 28:23.614
You're the pathetic one.

28:23.745 --> 28:25.268
The world may be toast,

28:25.399 --> 28:28.619
but at least I have happy
memories to keep me going.

28:28.750 --> 28:30.186
What the fuck do you have?

28:30.317 --> 28:33.320
Rations?
A septic system?

28:33.450 --> 28:35.452
You were so busy trying
to survive the end of the world,

28:35.583 --> 28:37.324
yours never got started.

28:37.454 --> 28:40.240
♪

28:40.370 --> 28:41.894
Fuck you.

28:42.024 --> 28:49.771
♪

28:49.902 --> 28:51.860
[Lamb bleats]

28:51.991 --> 28:54.689
May your next life
be blessed.

28:54.820 --> 29:02.001
♪

29:02.131 --> 29:09.225
♪

29:09.356 --> 29:11.097
[Walker growling]

29:11.227 --> 29:19.105
♪

29:19.235 --> 29:27.156
♪

29:27.287 --> 29:35.251
♪

29:35.382 --> 29:38.820
Joe: USHLDBSCRD.
[you should be scared]

29:38.951 --> 29:40.300
Hey.

29:40.430 --> 29:42.781
What --

29:42.911 --> 29:44.173
Oh, come on.

29:44.304 --> 29:46.872
Come on!

29:47.002 --> 29:48.003
What --

29:48.134 --> 29:50.049
[Herd growling]

29:50.179 --> 29:54.096
♪

29:54.227 --> 29:55.663
USHLDBSCRD!

29:55.794 --> 29:58.535
It's me! DotTheEye!

29:58.666 --> 29:59.754
You know me!

29:59.885 --> 30:02.409
I came to see if you're okay!

30:02.539 --> 30:04.628
I lost everything to get here!

30:04.759 --> 30:07.588
Yo! Yo!

30:07.718 --> 30:08.850
Yeah -- Oh.

30:08.981 --> 30:13.637
♪

30:13.768 --> 30:15.291
Whoa!

30:15.422 --> 30:16.510
[Groans]

30:17.946 --> 30:19.513
[Herd growling]

30:28.652 --> 30:31.220
[Buddy Holly's "Dearest"
playing in distance]

30:31.351 --> 30:33.092
♪ Dearest

30:33.222 --> 30:36.530
♪ Though you're the nearest
to my heart ♪

30:38.575 --> 30:42.492
♪ Please don't ever, ummm yeah

30:42.623 --> 30:45.408
♪ Ever say we'll part

30:47.019 --> 30:50.718
♪ You scold

30:50.849 --> 30:55.244
♪ And you're so bold

30:55.375 --> 30:58.030
DotTheEye?

30:58.160 --> 30:59.596
[Laughing] No.

30:59.727 --> 31:00.946
♪ Our love will grow old

31:01.076 --> 31:04.123
Figured out
you weren't in Alaska.

31:04.253 --> 31:07.691
I-I guess you can call me
Sandra now.

31:07.822 --> 31:09.780
I'm Joe.

31:09.911 --> 31:12.174
Holy shit,
it's really you.

31:12.305 --> 31:16.613
You never know what
you might find in person...

31:16.744 --> 31:20.487
♪ Please believe me, ummm yeah

31:20.617 --> 31:23.490
...but the apocalypse
has done you well.

31:23.620 --> 31:25.840
No. [Chuckles]

31:25.971 --> 31:29.278
No. Oh --
I'm all sweaty and gross.

31:29.409 --> 31:31.977
I was on the elliptical
and then the squats and --

31:32.107 --> 31:34.936
It's leg day. I --

31:35.067 --> 31:37.025
I don't know why
I'm telling you all this.

31:37.156 --> 31:40.637
I promised you a proper
sweet Buckeye if we ever met.

31:40.768 --> 31:42.988
[Both chuckle]

31:43.118 --> 31:44.337
Forgive me
for not bringing one.

31:44.467 --> 31:45.642
[Chuckles]

31:45.773 --> 31:47.470
I forgive you.
[Chuckles]

31:47.601 --> 31:49.298
♪

31:49.429 --> 31:50.604
Shit!

31:50.734 --> 31:53.433
Oh, I got you.

31:53.563 --> 31:55.522
I got you.

31:55.652 --> 31:58.090
[Buddy Holly's "Dearest"
continues playing in distance]

31:58.220 --> 32:03.138
♪

32:07.447 --> 32:12.887
♪

32:13.018 --> 32:18.197
♪

32:18.327 --> 32:19.763
Evie: Steven?

32:19.894 --> 32:27.597
♪

32:27.728 --> 32:29.556
[Lamb bleats]

32:29.686 --> 32:36.737
♪

32:36.867 --> 32:43.787
♪

32:43.918 --> 32:45.267
Hated.

32:45.398 --> 32:47.443
♪

32:47.574 --> 32:49.576
Hated.

32:49.706 --> 32:51.186
Definitely hated.

32:51.317 --> 32:54.059
♪

32:54.189 --> 32:57.366
[Gasps]

32:57.497 --> 32:59.586
Loved.

32:59.716 --> 33:04.765
♪

33:04.895 --> 33:09.726
♪

33:09.857 --> 33:12.599
I hope you made it.

33:12.729 --> 33:14.949
[Buddy Holly's
"Dearest"playing]

33:15.080 --> 33:17.256
This is gonna help me?

33:17.386 --> 33:20.433
It's not Betty Crocker's.
[Chuckles]

33:20.563 --> 33:23.175
♪ Dearest, though you're
the nearest to my heart ♪

33:23.305 --> 33:24.654
Oh, you must've had
such a long journey.

33:24.785 --> 33:26.221
Are you starving?

33:26.352 --> 33:28.658
I am just so happy
to see you.

33:28.789 --> 33:30.399
♪ Ever, ummm yeah,
ever say we'll part ♪

33:30.530 --> 33:34.273
Mm. You really like
this song, huh?

33:34.403 --> 33:35.491
♪

33:35.622 --> 33:37.058
I can flip
to the B-side.

33:37.189 --> 33:40.714
No.
It's...calming.

33:40.844 --> 33:42.977
♪ And you're so bold

33:43.108 --> 33:47.242
You know, I thought
about you this last year.

33:47.373 --> 33:49.853
A lot.

33:49.984 --> 33:52.726
More than a lot.

33:52.856 --> 33:55.294
I knew
you were a survivor,

33:55.424 --> 33:56.773
that you'd make it.

33:56.904 --> 33:59.689
But I didn't think
you'd actually look for me.

33:59.820 --> 34:02.692
Not in a million years.

34:02.823 --> 34:04.694
Neither did I.

34:04.825 --> 34:06.914
But, uh...

34:07.045 --> 34:08.872
my best friend,
Gilligan...

34:09.003 --> 34:11.484
Your dog, right?

34:11.614 --> 34:13.486
You remember.

34:13.616 --> 34:16.489
Well, he, uh --
I lost him.

34:16.619 --> 34:19.753
So I was alone,
and I got to thinking,

34:19.883 --> 34:22.016
it's hard to find people
you connect with, you know?

34:22.147 --> 34:23.887
And, uh...

34:24.018 --> 34:26.325
Sorry you lost Gilly.

34:26.455 --> 34:29.067
But I'm thankful
that it led you here.

34:30.503 --> 34:33.549
♪ Try my love again, ummm yeah

34:33.680 --> 34:35.943
It's getting late.

34:36.074 --> 34:38.511
Are you
spending the night?

34:38.641 --> 34:40.687
♪ I'm gonna treat you right

34:40.817 --> 34:43.864
I think the closest Best Western
is booked solid.

34:43.994 --> 34:46.214
[Both laugh]

34:46.345 --> 34:49.739
Hold on.
I, uh -- I have to freshen up.

34:49.870 --> 34:51.480
I wasn't expecting you,
obviously.

34:51.611 --> 34:53.700
[Chuckles]

34:53.830 --> 34:56.355
[Chuckles]
Okay.

34:56.485 --> 35:01.925
♪

35:02.056 --> 35:04.928
This is some strong stuff.

35:05.059 --> 35:08.410
[Echoing]
Let yourself go.

35:08.541 --> 35:10.412
See, that's the problem.

35:10.543 --> 35:14.373
I let myself go,
and I see some dark things.

35:14.503 --> 35:16.201
People I forgot.

35:16.331 --> 35:18.377
Or who forgot me.

35:18.507 --> 35:19.726
Jesus.

35:19.856 --> 35:22.120
This has a punch.

35:22.250 --> 35:24.774
Think of something happy.

35:24.905 --> 35:26.776
Think of Gilly.

35:26.907 --> 35:28.604
Think of football.

35:28.735 --> 35:30.780
♪ You scold

35:30.911 --> 35:31.955
♪ You scold, and -- You scold

35:32.086 --> 35:34.175
Sandra?

35:34.306 --> 35:37.135
[Echoing]
I'm here, darlin'.

35:37.265 --> 35:39.137
Can I have some water?

35:39.267 --> 35:40.616
[Distorted]
I wish I had met you

35:40.747 --> 35:44.968
when you were still
who you actually were.

35:45.099 --> 35:48.320
We coulda been happy.

35:48.450 --> 35:51.671
Ooh! Wha--

35:51.801 --> 35:54.369
W-What's this for?

35:54.500 --> 35:56.241
For a game.

35:56.371 --> 35:58.547
[Distorted]
You'll like it.

35:58.678 --> 36:00.375
Oh, okay.

36:00.506 --> 36:02.769
[Both chuckle]

36:02.899 --> 36:05.772
Why are you here?

36:05.902 --> 36:07.774
Can you loosen these,
please?

36:07.904 --> 36:10.951
♪

36:11.081 --> 36:12.213
Hey.

36:14.041 --> 36:16.217
Hey! Aah.

36:16.348 --> 36:19.916
Why are you here, Joe?

36:20.047 --> 36:22.267
To find you!

36:22.397 --> 36:24.791
Why?

36:24.921 --> 36:27.141
You want my place,
don't you?

36:27.272 --> 36:28.838
What?! No!

36:28.969 --> 36:31.450
I want you!

36:31.580 --> 36:35.410
I don't believe you!!

36:35.541 --> 36:36.629
Ow!

36:39.240 --> 36:41.024
[Lamb bleats]

36:41.155 --> 36:48.031
♪

36:48.162 --> 36:49.642
♪ Please don't ever

36:49.772 --> 36:51.557
Sandra: The first few months
down here were tough.

36:51.687 --> 36:53.863
Not the staying alive part.
That was easy.

36:53.994 --> 36:55.648
Obviously, I was prepared.

36:55.778 --> 36:58.433
[Distorted]
Ignoring all the screams?

36:58.564 --> 37:00.348
That was the hard part.

37:00.479 --> 37:02.307
[Slurring]
You did what you had to do.

37:02.437 --> 37:05.092
♪ You're so bold

37:05.223 --> 37:07.573
People,
they would find me here.

37:07.703 --> 37:11.359
They would bang on my door,
they'd plead.

37:11.490 --> 37:13.840
So I started listening
to the music.

37:13.970 --> 37:16.146
[Distorted]
♪ Our love will grow old

37:16.277 --> 37:19.672
[Distorted]
The music saved me.

37:19.802 --> 37:20.934
♪ You may-ay-ay-ay be

37:21.064 --> 37:22.283
One night, um,

37:22.414 --> 37:24.851
a man, he, uh --

37:24.981 --> 37:27.506
he got in.

37:27.636 --> 37:28.985
[Scoffs]

37:29.116 --> 37:31.292
Do you think he was friendly?
Neighborly? Hell no.

37:31.423 --> 37:33.903
Do you think
that he would kill me

37:34.034 --> 37:36.645
and steal
all that I had built?

37:36.776 --> 37:38.734
Hell yes.

37:38.865 --> 37:41.955
I didn't have a choice.

37:42.085 --> 37:43.086
Who could blame you?

37:43.217 --> 37:44.958
He had a nice watch.

37:45.088 --> 37:47.134
I liked the way it glimmered,
so I kept it.

37:47.265 --> 37:48.918
♪ Keep me from
these sleepless nights ♪

37:49.049 --> 37:51.269
But one is never enough.

37:51.399 --> 37:56.012
♪ Try my love again, ummm yeah

37:56.143 --> 37:58.754
♪ I'm gonna treat you right

37:58.885 --> 38:00.756
♪ Ummm yeah,
I'm gonna treat you right ♪

38:00.887 --> 38:02.976
I still hear the screams.

38:03.106 --> 38:04.543
[Distorted]
I already hear yours.

38:04.673 --> 38:06.893
No!

38:07.023 --> 38:08.329
What the fuck?

38:08.460 --> 38:10.331
[Both grunting]

38:10.462 --> 38:12.899
♪

38:13.029 --> 38:15.902
[Screaming]

38:16.032 --> 38:22.125
♪

38:22.256 --> 38:28.436
♪

38:28.567 --> 38:31.004
I'll scream for you
if I have to.

38:31.134 --> 38:33.659
[Motion sensor alarms beeping]

38:37.271 --> 38:39.708
You didn't come alone.

38:39.839 --> 38:41.493
I did.
Bullshit!

38:41.623 --> 38:43.582
Liar!

38:43.712 --> 38:45.801
This was your plan.
To snake me out

38:45.932 --> 38:50.153
and take all of it
for you and your whore.

38:50.284 --> 38:52.765
[Alarms continue beeping]

38:52.895 --> 38:54.810
[Panting]

39:00.990 --> 39:03.036
[Grunts]

39:03.166 --> 39:04.777
[Whispering] Joe!

39:08.084 --> 39:09.695
Joe!

39:13.307 --> 39:16.136
[Quietly] Ma'am?

39:16.266 --> 39:17.746
USHLDBSCRD?

39:17.877 --> 39:20.619
Is that a question
or a warning?

39:20.749 --> 39:21.707
[Gasps]

39:21.837 --> 39:22.969
Both.

39:23.099 --> 39:25.885
Then yes and yes.

39:26.015 --> 39:28.801
A storm of dead-eyes
are gonna be hitting here soon.

39:28.931 --> 39:30.150
You should come with me.

39:30.280 --> 39:36.591
♪

39:41.640 --> 39:43.337
Hungry?

39:43.468 --> 39:44.686
Oh.

39:44.817 --> 39:46.035
Thanks.

39:46.166 --> 39:49.865
♪ Ummm yeah,
our love will grow old ♪

39:49.996 --> 39:51.867
That's really good.

39:51.998 --> 39:53.347
It's homemade.

39:53.478 --> 39:55.262
[Chuckles]

39:55.393 --> 39:59.222
Uh, so how far
did you travel on foot?

39:59.353 --> 40:01.486
15 miles.

40:01.616 --> 40:04.053
Kick your boots off.

40:04.184 --> 40:05.664
It's alright.

40:05.794 --> 40:07.143
♪ Please believe me

40:07.274 --> 40:09.842
So, how --
how did you know my handle?

40:09.972 --> 40:11.234
Did we chat?

40:11.365 --> 40:13.672
No, um...

40:13.802 --> 40:15.978
You know my friend Joe.

40:16.109 --> 40:18.633
Joe?

40:18.764 --> 40:20.287
It doesn't ring a bell.

40:21.157 --> 40:24.117
Uh, he's a grump.

40:24.247 --> 40:26.293
Um, he likes the football.

40:26.424 --> 40:28.077
Iowa or something.

40:28.208 --> 40:29.731
[Grunts] Huh?

40:29.862 --> 40:31.907
Rings a bell.

40:32.038 --> 40:34.649
Um, it was Ohio, I think.

40:34.780 --> 40:35.911
So you doknow him?

40:36.042 --> 40:36.956
[Lamb bleats]

40:37.086 --> 40:38.610
[Chuckles]

40:38.740 --> 40:40.394
♪

40:40.525 --> 40:44.137
Uh, I think I remember.

40:44.267 --> 40:47.401
[Chuckles]
He came all this way for me?

40:47.532 --> 40:49.403
Um...

40:49.534 --> 40:51.840
Well, he didn't, though.

40:51.971 --> 40:54.887
I don-- I don't mean
to be callous, but

40:55.017 --> 40:57.324
maybe he...

40:57.455 --> 41:00.283
Maybe he didn't make it.

41:00.414 --> 41:02.285
No, he had to.

41:02.416 --> 41:04.157
He --

41:04.287 --> 41:06.507
He just had to.

41:06.638 --> 41:08.901
He's a survivor.

41:09.031 --> 41:11.512
He is, yes.

41:11.643 --> 41:13.296
Yes, isn't he?
[Chuckles]

41:13.427 --> 41:15.516
How are you feeling?

41:15.647 --> 41:16.909
Relaxed?

41:17.039 --> 41:18.737
Should I be?

41:18.867 --> 41:20.390
Have some more.

41:24.960 --> 41:26.484
You know, it's shady
to give someone an edible

41:26.614 --> 41:28.921
without telling them.

41:29.051 --> 41:31.184
Edible? What?

41:31.314 --> 41:33.926
I'm a connoisseur.

41:34.056 --> 41:36.319
And you've been lying
this whole time.

41:36.450 --> 41:38.539
[Both grunting]

41:38.670 --> 41:42.064
♪

41:42.195 --> 41:44.545
Ohh!
[Groaning]

41:44.676 --> 41:47.287
♪

41:47.417 --> 41:49.115
[Joe screaming, muffled]

41:49.245 --> 41:55.208
♪

41:55.338 --> 41:56.688
Oh. Oh, my God.

41:56.818 --> 41:59.778
♪

41:59.908 --> 42:02.041
[Sandra screaming]

42:02.171 --> 42:05.435
♪

42:07.481 --> 42:08.961
Oh.

42:13.661 --> 42:15.663
[Lamb bleats]

42:18.144 --> 42:19.972
Can we get outta here?

42:20.102 --> 42:22.148
Please.

42:22.278 --> 42:23.932
[Giggles] Look.

42:24.063 --> 42:26.456
Oh.
Did you eat her brownies?

42:26.587 --> 42:29.459
[Straining] No rush!
You're light as a feather.

42:29.590 --> 42:31.810
Come on.[Walker growling]

42:31.940 --> 42:34.639
God, this bitch won't quit!

42:34.769 --> 42:36.728
Come on. Come on.

42:36.858 --> 42:39.905
♪

42:40.035 --> 42:41.602
Aah!

42:41.733 --> 42:44.344
♪

42:44.474 --> 42:47.129
[Both panting]

42:49.218 --> 42:51.003
And you thought
Steven was a dick?

42:55.747 --> 42:57.575
So, you find him?

42:59.185 --> 43:00.708
No.

43:02.754 --> 43:04.059
But that's okay.

43:08.194 --> 43:10.631
[Giggling]

43:12.677 --> 43:14.983
Why am I so hungry?

43:15.114 --> 43:17.682
[Giggling]

43:17.812 --> 43:20.119
[Laughing]
W-What is happening?

43:20.249 --> 43:22.512
[Continues laughing]

43:22.643 --> 43:24.863
That was fuckin' dramatic.

43:24.993 --> 43:29.302
♪

43:35.438 --> 43:37.527
[Birds chirping]

43:42.794 --> 43:45.231
[Lamb bleats]

43:45.361 --> 43:46.667
Evie: [Whispering] Joe?

43:50.584 --> 43:52.107
Joe?

43:57.809 --> 43:59.549
Evie:
I thought you left.

44:01.029 --> 44:04.032
Mother nature.

44:04.163 --> 44:05.164
Why'd you think I left?

44:05.294 --> 44:07.296
Maybe you remembered
you were a loner

44:07.427 --> 44:10.735
or maybe...

44:10.865 --> 44:11.997
I don't know.

44:13.172 --> 44:15.435
I never thanked you
for coming back.

44:16.610 --> 44:18.133
You don't have to.

44:19.178 --> 44:21.702
Thank you.

44:21.833 --> 44:26.272
♪

44:26.402 --> 44:28.100
Stupid...

44:28.230 --> 44:32.147
♪

44:32.278 --> 44:34.323
My life...

44:34.454 --> 44:36.369
It never got started.

44:36.499 --> 44:38.588
I had something precious,

44:38.719 --> 44:41.940
and I did everything to make
sure no one could touch it.

44:42.070 --> 44:44.594
♪

44:44.725 --> 44:46.858
I made it worthless
that way, Evie.

44:46.988 --> 44:51.210
♪

44:51.340 --> 44:52.864
The hell I do?

44:52.994 --> 44:57.346
♪

44:57.477 --> 44:59.566
So start now.

44:59.697 --> 45:02.134
What?
It's not over.

45:02.264 --> 45:06.051
You have a person
standing right in front of you.

45:06.181 --> 45:08.357
I mean, maybe there's more
out there, too.

45:08.488 --> 45:10.185
I mean, look around.

45:10.316 --> 45:15.887
You are a part of this
screwed-up, beautiful place.

45:16.017 --> 45:19.107
♪

45:19.238 --> 45:20.805
Beautiful?

45:20.935 --> 45:24.243
Well, like -- Well, not here.

45:24.373 --> 45:25.766
Out there.

45:25.897 --> 45:30.162
♪

45:30.292 --> 45:32.207
[Lamb bleats]

45:32.338 --> 45:33.992
She got a name?

45:34.122 --> 45:35.123
Not yet.

45:35.254 --> 45:38.170
Any ideas?

45:38.300 --> 45:39.737
Skipper?

45:39.867 --> 45:41.521
♪

45:41.651 --> 45:43.349
[Skipper bleats]

45:43.479 --> 45:52.924
♪

45:53.054 --> 46:02.977
♪

46:06.938 --> 46:08.504
Man: I heard people who
are attacking people --

46:08.635 --> 46:11.638
scratching, biting.

46:11.769 --> 46:13.466
People need to chill.
Everybody's fine.

46:13.596 --> 46:14.989
[Tires squealing]

46:15.120 --> 46:16.425
What?!
You're fired.

46:16.556 --> 46:18.036
[Screaming]

46:18.166 --> 46:20.386
People are going crazy.

46:20.516 --> 46:23.389
Have you ever had
a really bad déjà vu?

46:23.519 --> 46:24.607
[Tires squealing]

46:24.738 --> 46:25.957
[Women screaming]

46:26.087 --> 46:27.785
[Telephone ringing]

46:27.915 --> 46:29.090
Go to hell!

46:29.221 --> 46:30.309
We're already there!

46:30.439 --> 46:31.745
[Screams]

46:31.876 --> 46:35.009
♪

46:36.489 --> 46:46.238
♪

46:46.368 --> 46:55.987
♪

